then it has the multinomial distribution as follows
$$
\begin{aligned}
&P\left[X_1=s_1, X_2=s_2, \ldots, X_k=s_m\right]=\left\{\begin{array}{l}
\frac{n!}{s_{1}!s_{2}!\ldots s_{m}!} p_1^{s_1} p_2^{s_2} \ldots p_m^{s_k} \\
0 \quad \ \text { otherwise }
\end{array}\right.\\
&\ \text { where } s_i=0,1, \ldots, n \ \text { and } \sum_{i=1}^m s_i=n .
\end{aligned}
$$
